posts.body: I've been going back to TF2. I tried Joining a CK2 multiplayer campaign, but everyone there had low commitments and barely made it to the first session. I wish I actually had people to play CK2 with for grand goals like forming the HRE/Restoring Byzantium. **If this is what does in the site, then I am so fucked. no place to vent, and I'll be permanently forced to be a mundane faggot** **The backup plan should've been advertised better, It needs to be advertised better if the site makes it through this clusterfuck**

I feel like I need to have my computer on 24/7 like a Seedbox for this place to functon properly. I, however, still like this site's premise and how any DoS attack would be useless on this site. This place needs to be more heavily advertised as a proper backup when the main site goes back up. We've been too complacent when we shouldn't have even with shit like the April Fools Hack not giving a cause for concern and now everyone's been scattered again badly.

>>f41da36e-2cec-4c86-b2da-4e4d279b1478
Yeah, I think it helps to go without TOR **Or a VPN** but that has it's own potential risks. It might also help to just leave your computer on when not in use, but I get the feeling everyone on this site already does that.

>>10f0d872-9007-43c2-a894-fead48f27fa2
More than likely your network is just being strained. It alreadly has to bounce around a bunch of TOR Peers and now you're using it as a sort of Torrent Client for ZeroNet.

>8chan will stay down until after Jim's congressional testimony according to BitMitigate. Epik is still the DNS provider and domain registrar.

How long do we have to wait for that? I'm dreading this'll be a good month.

>>f44ca50f-f56e-43d7-9cd7-c17b42417707
Gotta treat this place like a massive torrent. can't turn off the computer until you know someone else has it. Though how you'll know is the real question.

the faster you mute that faggot, the less people have to see him. I wish there was a mute function in the catalog to make this shit easier. I'm going to dread what this place will look like come morning.

I still remember My Level 60 FOMar account on that server, though I haven't logged in a while. I kept trying to play with my brother until other games caught interest. I really need to log back in and at least beat episode 1 proper.

>Funnily enough, your image won't open for me. I can see the thumbnail though..
He forgot to leave his computer on to seed it for a while, that should be fixed next time he's online.

>>6a0ed448-93dd-418c-9d2e-e783ba8190b2
>Or just go in the catalog and bump the best threads back to the top. That's what others have been doing.
that'll just keep the clutter and make future peers have to look at it. I'm not even sure if bumping works similar to the clearnet board since post numbers are different for everyone on this site. The more people mute them the less chance future peers that find this site will see the spam and think the board is dead. Just go to the board homepage, not the catalog, and start muting to make things easier.
